# Supabase / Vercel environment variables template
# Copy these lines into Vercel's "Import .env" box or add individually.
# Replace placeholders with your project's real values.

# Supabase public URL (example: https://xyz.supabase.co)
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co

# Supabase service role key (server-only secret). Keep this SAFE.
# Do NOT expose this value to the browser or client-side code.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGciOi...your_service_role_key_here...

# Toggle Supabase mode in the frontend (1 to enable)
NEXT_PUBLIC_USE_SUPABASE=1

# Optional: anon key if you need client-only access for some features
# PUBLIC_ANON_KEY=your_anon_key_here

# Notes:
# - In Vercel, set SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY as Sensitive (server-only).
# - Variables prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_ are exposed to the browser.
# - After adding variables in Vercel, trigger a redeploy or push a new commit.
